19.3 Severability. If any provision is held unenforceable, it shall be modified
     to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, and the remaining
     provisions shall continue in full force.

19.4 Waiver. Failure to enforce any provision is not a waiver of future
     enforcement of that or any other provision. Waivers must be in writing
     to be effective.

19.5 Relationship. Nothing in this Agreement creates a partnership, joint
     venture, employment, or agency relationship between the parties.

19.6 Notices. Notices under this Agreement may be delivered by email or written
     notice to the contacts designated by each party, and via the contact method
